title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return recognizable strings
OB: Before extraction, when calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel(), the labels returned are null. However, after extraction, the labels returned are recognizable strings.
EB: The expected behavior is for IMetaData.getColumnLabel() to always return recognizable strings, both before and after data extraction.
SR: To reproduce the issue, follow these steps: 1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction. 2. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() after data extraction. Compare the results and notice the difference.
